PATHOLOGIST: Hawksley, Carlene A. M.D. Clinical History:
BARRETT'S ESOPHAGUS
Source:
1. Distal esophagus biopsy
Gross Description:
1. The specimen is received in a single formalin-filled container labeled 'HOLDEN, MARK; distal esophagus biopsy' and consists of three light-tan fragments of tissue ranging in size from 0.2 to 0.3 cm in maximum dimension. The specimen is filtered, marked with hematoxylin, wrapped and totally submitted in one cassette. CB:km
Diagnosis:
1. DISTAL ESOPHAGUS, BIOPSIES: A. SQUAMOGLANDULAR MUCOSA WITH PROMINENT SQUAMOUS HYPERPLASIA, BASAL CELL HYPERPLASIA, AND INTRAEPITHELIAL MIXED LYMPHOCYTIC AND EOSINOPHILIC INFLAMMATION OF SQUAMOUS EPITHELIUM; CONSISTENT WITH CHRONIC REFLUX ESOPHAGITIS. B. FOCAL PANCREATIC ACINAR METAPLASIA OF GLANDULAR EPITHELIUM BUT NO EVIDENCE OF INTESTINAL METAPLASIA OR OTHER FEATURES DIAGNOSTIC OF BARRETT'S ESOPHAGUS IDENTIFIED. C. MILD INFLAMMATORY EPITHELIAL ATYPIA WITH NO EVIDENCE OF DYSPLASIA OR MALIGNANCY. D. NO EVIDENCE OF EOSINOPHILIC ESOPHAGITIS, VIRAL INCLUSION BODIES, OR FUNGAL ORGANISMS IDENTIFIED ON PAS STAINED SECTIONS.
Comment:
1. Dr. Quinn has reviewed the case and concurs with the diagnosis.

OPERATIVE REPORT
PATIENT NAME: HOLDEN, MARK MEDICAL RECORD #: 0019034
SURGEON: TRETA PUROHIT GOYAL, M.D. DATE OF SURGERY: 09/29/2016
GENDER: M DATE OF BIRTH: 06/18/1965
PROCEDURE PERFORMED: EGD.
ANESTHESIA: MAC.
ANESTHESIOLOGIST: Mark Rigler, M.D.
INDICATIONS FOR PROCEDURE: History of Barrett's esophagus.
OPERATIVE PROCEDURE: Procedure was performed under monitored anesthesia care because of Norco use. After the time-out, the GIF scope was passed through the oropharynx into the esophagus. Two small salmon-colored tongues were noted at the GE junction suggestive of Barrett's esophagus, these were biopsied. Moderate amount of pale fluid in the stomach, this was suctioned, likely secondary to gastroparesis due to chronic opioid use. Normal stomach, duodenum in the bulb and the second portion.
IMPRESSION: Short-segment Barrett's esophagus, biopsied.
RECOMMENDATIONS: Call Dr. Goyal's office at (831) 621-5055 for questions or concerns. Continue daily Prilosec. We will follow up biopsy results. Repeat EGD in one to three years for Barrett's surveillance based on the biopsy results.
X_______________________ Treta Purohit Goyal, M.D.
